algorithms.paths

Class DP_Anyk_Iterator

  • java.lang.Object
    • algorithms.paths.DP_Anyk_Iterator
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    DP_Part, DP_Recursive, Path_Batch

    public abstract class DP_Anyk_Iterator
extends Object
    A ranked enumeration algorithm for a DP problem specified by a DP_Problem_Instance object. It is implemented as an iterator that is first initialized and then the method get_next() returns the next best DP solution in ranked order. This is an abstract class: to instantiate it, a subclass that implements get_next() must be provided.

    IMPORTANT: Before using this class, DP_Problem_Instance.bottom_up() must have already been run on the DP instance.
    Author:
    Nikolaos Tziavelis
